  "title": "Senior Business Analyst (Insurance / Agile)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Role Overview</strong></u></p><p>Drive business requirements and delivery alignment for insurance digital transformation programs. Bridge business stakeholders and Agile delivery teams.<br /><br /><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Gather and document business requirements and user stories</li><li>Facilitate workshops, process mapping, gap analysis</li><li>Support backlog grooming, sprint planning, UAT</li><li>Coordinate with Product Owners, Developers, QA</li><li>Ensure regulatory and operational compliance</li><li>Support go-live and change management</li></ul><p><strong>Mandatory Skills</strong></p><ul><li>5+ years Business Analysis in Insurance</li><li>Strong knowledge of policy lifecycle, claims, billing</li><li>Agile / Scrum delivery experience</li><li>Excellent stakeholder management and documentation skills</li><li>Insurance Policy Admin System (PAS) exposure</li><li>Tools: Jira, Confluence, Visio</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred</strong></p><ul><li>API / digital platform understanding</li><li>MAS / compliance familiarity</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Qualifications:</strong></u><br /><br /><strong>Education:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field</li><li>PMI - PBA certification or equivalent</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Full-time position</li><li>Standard office hours with potential for occasional overtime</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Equal Opportunity Employer:</strong></u></p><ul><li>III is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.</li></ul>",
